10 SECTION 6. Section 73-20-18 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1957,
11 Chapter 210, Section 17, as amended) is amended to read:
12 "73-20-18. ASSESSMENT LISTS.--
13 A. The board of directors shall prepare a list of
14 the landowners within the defined boundaries of the watershed
15 district in each county involved showing the number of acres
16 subject to assessment and deliver it to the county assessor
17 of the county involved. The assessor shall indicate the
18 information on the tax rolls.
19 B. The county assessor shall compute the
assessment due the district from each landowner in accordance
20
with the rate fixed by the board of supervisors and the value
21
of the real property indicated on the tax roll. The
22
computation shall be made on the regular tax bills in the
23
manner as may be directed by regulation of the property tax
24
division of the taxation and revenue department."
