1 SECTION 7. Section 73-20-20 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1957,
2 Chapter 210, Section 19, as amended) is amended to read:
3 "73-20-20. EXPENDITURES.--Assessment funds collected
4 shall be transferred to and held by the treasurer of the
5 watershed district for the specific purpose for which they
6 have been collected. All expenditures of such funds shall be
7 made by the board of directors upon order and approval of the
8 board of supervisors of the soil and water conservation
9 district involved."
10 SECTION 8. Section 73-20-45 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1965,
11 Chapter 137, Section 19, as amended) is amended to read:
12 "73-20-45. SPECIFIC POWERS OF DISTRICTS.--A district,
13 by and through its supervisors, is authorized to:
14 A. sue and be sued in the name of the district;
15 B. adopt an official seal;
16 C. contract, convey and make and execute other
17 instruments and documents necessary or convenient to the
18 exercise of district powers;
19 D. borrow money and otherwise contract
20 indebtedness for the purposes of the district and, without
limitation of the generality of the foregoing, borrow money
21
and accept grants from the United States or from a
22
corporation or agency created or designated by the United
23
States and, in connection with any such loan or grant, enter
24
into agreements as the United States or the corporation or
25 HB 108/a
Page 8

1 agency may require; and issue its notes or obligations
2 therefor and secure the payment thereof by mortgage, pledge
3 or deed of trust of all or any of its property, assets,
4 rights, privileges, licenses, rights of way, easements,
5 revenues or income;
6 E. option, as optionee and optioner, and acquire,
7 in any manner, real and personal property or any right or
8 interest in it;
9 F. improve, rent, lease and sell district property
10 or any interest in it;
11 G. receive, invest and reinvest rents and income
12 from district property and expend rents and income for
13 district purposes;
14 H. accept contributions, gifts and donations and
